Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York and New Jersey:
• In Southport, Conn., a five-bedroom, four-and-a-half-bath, fully renovated 1845 house with a living room with fireplace, a formal dining room, an eat-in kitchen with marble counters, a master suite with balcony, a third-floor entertainment room, a temperature-controlled wine cellar, a bluestone patio, a whole-house generator and a detached two-car garage, on 0.36 acres.
• In Irvington, N.Y., a four-bedroom, two-and-a-half-bath 1985 house with a two-sided fireplace in the living room/family room, a screened-in porch with wood-burning stove and a finished lower level, on 0.48 acre near Halsey Pond.
